Video Game Genres

Role Playing Game (RPG)
Loosely defined, an RPG is a game that allows the player to identify as the character they are playing. This can take many different forms, from extensive character customization and creation to giving the player decisions through their character.
Notable characteristics:
  Player character given freedom and choices in the game that are meaningful.
  Player can choose between different classes (warrior, mage, archer, etc.).
  Character customization.

